WEBVTT

00:00:36.536 --> 00:00:37.996
{\an8}Why did you call out of the blue?

00:00:38.079 --> 00:00:39.581
{\an8}Can we go out for dinner?

00:00:39.664 --> 00:00:41.374
{\an8}- Are you okay? - Of course.

00:00:41.458 --> 00:00:43.293
{\an8}You're acting so weird.

00:00:43.376 --> 00:00:46.254
{\an8}<i>You suddenly call</i> <i>and ask me to watch a movie.</i>

00:00:46.337 --> 00:00:47.380
{\an8}<i>Are you dying?</i>

00:01:12.822 --> 00:01:14.365
‪Oh wow.

00:01:32.091 --> 00:01:33.468
{\an8}That's enough.

00:01:34.052 --> 00:01:36.638
{\an8}Viktor, you two don't understand each other anymore.

00:01:36.721 --> 00:01:38.723
{\an8}Neither of you wants to lose.

00:01:38.807 --> 00:01:41.351
{\an8}Like father, like daughter.

00:01:46.648 --> 00:01:47.732
{\an8}And you.

00:01:48.942 --> 00:01:50.860
{\an8}Cool off first, okay?

00:02:24.978 --> 00:02:28.022
{\an8}Knowing the Moravianos, they won't move without direction.

00:02:28.815 --> 00:02:30.650
{\an8}Clearly, they have a target.

00:02:31.860 --> 00:02:34.529
{\an8}Which is my close friend?

00:02:36.030 --> 00:02:39.450
{\an8}And when you're their target, they aim to kill you

00:02:39.534 --> 00:02:41.744
{\an8}because you're a thorn in their side.

00:02:43.204 --> 00:02:45.039
{\an8}Am I understanding it correctly?

00:02:45.123 --> 00:02:50.253
{\an8}Because of my close friend, who, thank God, is alive and kicking,

00:02:51.129 --> 00:02:53.882
{\an8}our mission will become easier

00:02:53.965 --> 00:02:58.303
{\an8}and we'll learn more about the Moravianos?

00:03:12.775 --> 00:03:17.614
You've already spent so much time building a case against them, remember?

00:03:27.290 --> 00:03:31.753
May all the favors be in your favor, dear.

00:03:31.836 --> 00:03:36.007
Cheers! To the final mission.

00:03:49.187 --> 00:03:50.104
I can see it

00:03:50.188 --> 00:03:51.356
I'm manifesting it already.

00:03:51.439 --> 00:03:54.192
Cheers to my future grandmother era!

00:03:54.275 --> 00:03:57.612
That's if you want to start a family right away.

00:03:57.695 --> 00:03:59.948
If not, then don't rush.

00:04:00.031 --> 00:04:02.033
That's okay too.

00:04:10.833 --> 00:04:14.295
Isn't it true that in this world,

00:04:15.004 --> 00:04:20.385
This world of the mafia, the only way out is death?

00:04:32.272 --> 00:04:35.233
Even if, let's say, I do finish the mission,

00:04:36.109 --> 00:04:40.196
And Mikoy and I are allowed to live the normal life I've been dreaming of,

00:04:41.948 --> 00:04:44.409
I can never escape this kind of life.

00:04:45.618 --> 00:04:47.745
I'll always be a Moraviano.

00:04:57.547 --> 00:05:01.134
Are you sure about putting me back in my position?

00:05:02.844 --> 00:05:04.512
I'm absolutely sure.

00:05:04.595 --> 00:05:06.681
But are you sure you want to come back,

00:05:06.764 --> 00:05:08.808
Knowing there's a threat to your life?

00:05:08.891 --> 00:05:10.810
It's part of the job.

00:05:12.395 --> 00:05:14.772
I know your line of work is dangerous,

00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:20.028
But sometimes I forget that danger can come anytime, anywhere.

00:05:20.111 --> 00:05:23.239
Right now, we're talking, we're laughing.

00:05:23.323 --> 00:05:27.285
The next moment, you don't know what could happen.

00:05:27.994 --> 00:05:29.329
Well, that's true.

00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:33.958
Even after spending decades in this line of work,

00:05:34.042 --> 00:05:37.712
It's different when death is already near.

00:05:39.338 --> 00:05:40.548
Are you scared now?

00:05:42.008 --> 00:05:43.134
Not really.

00:05:44.635 --> 00:05:45.678
But

00:05:47.680 --> 00:05:50.183
Earlier, when I was with Sofie,

00:05:51.642 --> 00:05:57.565
I kind of felt nervous.

00:05:59.734 --> 00:06:02.820
Good thing nothing bad happened.

00:06:02.904 --> 00:06:05.531
Good thing it still wasn't my time.

00:06:05.615 --> 00:06:07.492
You know me.

00:06:08.117 --> 00:06:12.580
I'm ready for anything, but what I can't accept

00:06:12.663 --> 00:06:14.916
Is my daughter getting involved.

00:06:14.999 --> 00:06:17.293
I don't want her to get involved

00:06:17.376 --> 00:06:21.798
Just because I chose this life.

00:06:21.881 --> 00:06:24.634
That's wishful thinking, my friend.

00:06:24.717 --> 00:06:26.010
Exactly.

00:06:26.094 --> 00:06:31.474
I know it will benefit Sofie and her generation eventually,

00:06:31.974 --> 00:06:34.685
Even if I no longer get to witness it.

00:06:34.769 --> 00:06:36.938
What's important is,

00:06:39.482 --> 00:06:41.317
I did a great job.

00:06:50.701 --> 00:06:53.371
<i>Even if, let's say,</i> <i>I do finish the mission,</i>

00:06:53.454 --> 00:06:57.667
<i>and Mikoy and I are allowed to live</i> <i>the normal life I've been dreaming of,</i>

00:06:58.417 --> 00:07:00.711
<i>I can never escape this life.</i>

00:07:02.046 --> 00:07:04.215
<i>I'll always be a Moraviano.</i>

00:07:37.123 --> 00:07:41.794
Chiara, why? Is there a problem?

00:07:43.838 --> 00:07:44.839
No.

00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:47.717
I just wanted to hear your voice.

00:07:48.301 --> 00:07:49.677
Really?

00:07:49.760 --> 00:07:53.806
We've only been apart for a few hours, and you already miss me?

00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:56.684
I don't know.

00:07:57.852 --> 00:08:00.146
I don't know why I miss you so much already.

00:08:01.022 --> 00:08:02.482
<i>I just want to</i>

00:08:03.316 --> 00:08:06.527
See you and hug you right now.

00:08:07.612 --> 00:08:09.739
When I'm with you,

00:08:10.740 --> 00:08:15.161
I feel at ease, like I'm always safe.

00:08:22.960 --> 00:08:24.295
Is there a problem?

00:08:26.714 --> 00:08:27.715
<i>Just tell me.</i>

00:08:27.798 --> 00:08:31.344
I'll listen with no judgment.

00:08:32.845 --> 00:08:34.013
Really?

00:08:36.682 --> 00:08:38.100
<i>Of course!</i>

00:08:38.893 --> 00:08:40.770
Chiara, I love you so much.

00:08:40.853 --> 00:08:43.981
I accept you as you are, okay?

00:08:47.235 --> 00:08:48.236
You know that.

00:08:50.488 --> 00:08:52.156
<i>Did something happen?</i>

00:08:58.913 --> 00:09:02.250
What can I do to help? Come on.

00:09:06.087 --> 00:09:07.213
Nothing.

00:09:10.424 --> 00:09:11.717
I'm just tired.

00:09:16.556 --> 00:09:20.476
I just wanted to talk to you and hear your voice before I sleep.

00:09:21.477 --> 00:09:26.857
Well, even in your dreams, you can definitely talk to me. Okay?

00:09:28.442 --> 00:09:30.611
Talk to you in my dreams?

00:09:33.114 --> 00:09:35.700
Sweet dreams, love, and I'll be there.

00:09:36.701 --> 00:09:38.578
Come on now. Good night.

00:11:09.877 --> 00:11:14.465
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

00:11:22.973 --> 00:11:24.725
As you can see,

00:11:24.809 --> 00:11:27.311
Around this time, General Ruiz arrived,

00:11:28.312 --> 00:11:31.190
And this is the park's peak hours.

00:11:32.608 --> 00:11:35.653
There were so many people. It was overwhelming.

00:11:45.538 --> 00:11:50.876
Maybe there wasn't actually any imminent danger last night, Agent Alex.

00:11:55.047 --> 00:11:58.384
But maybe we're looking at nothing.

00:11:58.968 --> 00:12:02.972
All this footage and prospects Maybe we're just

00:12:05.307 --> 00:12:07.977
Overreacting?

00:12:08.060 --> 00:12:10.396
Being prepared matters more than working hard,

00:12:10.479 --> 00:12:14.024
But the one who overreacts and overthinks beats them all.

00:12:51.854 --> 00:12:54.064
Oh, no way.

00:12:55.649 --> 00:12:57.693
What a nice way to wake up.

00:12:58.444 --> 00:13:00.696
But is this for real?

00:13:03.949 --> 00:13:05.910
Oh! It really is!

00:13:06.702 --> 00:13:09.830
Wait, am I still dreaming?

00:13:10.331 --> 00:13:13.250
Of course not, I'm really here.

00:13:15.419 --> 00:13:18.214
You really missed me that much

00:13:18.797 --> 00:13:22.134
That you just casually walked into my room.

00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:30.392
You know that's an invasion of privacy, right?

00:13:31.519 --> 00:13:34.813
And you didn't even ask for consent.

00:13:35.314 --> 00:13:37.191
I could sue you.

00:13:38.150 --> 00:13:39.276
You know that?

00:13:43.072 --> 00:13:44.740
So it's better

00:13:47.201 --> 00:13:48.619
You should just live here.

00:13:50.204 --> 00:13:51.497
With me.

00:13:58.087 --> 00:13:59.505
Are you serious?

00:14:06.178 --> 00:14:07.137
Of course.

00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:13.477
So it's not that obvious that I always want to be with you.

00:14:14.311 --> 00:14:17.565
I feel guilty whenever I need you

00:14:17.648 --> 00:14:20.568
Or when you need me and we're miles apart.

00:14:21.819 --> 00:14:24.238
Sweetheart, it feels like my heart wants to burst

00:14:24.321 --> 00:14:28.659
Whenever you're sad and I can't even hug you.

00:14:28.742 --> 00:14:32.162
You know that? That's so hard.

00:14:32.246 --> 00:14:33.873
I can't do this.

00:14:35.791 --> 00:14:37.209
So, please?

00:14:40.212 --> 00:14:41.630
Mikoy!

00:14:42.172 --> 00:14:43.424
Mikoy!

00:14:48.387 --> 00:14:51.932
Because of that, this calls for a celebration!

00:14:52.016 --> 00:14:53.225
Okay.

00:14:53.309 --> 00:14:54.560
So, I'm staying here now?

00:15:13.621 --> 00:15:14.872
Sofie.

00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:19.835
I thought

00:15:19.919 --> 00:15:21.295
Do you have enemies?

00:15:21.378 --> 00:15:22.838
Why were you in defense mode?

00:15:25.382 --> 00:15:26.926
Especially these days.

00:15:27.009 --> 00:15:29.386
Are you part of the boxing team?

00:15:29.470 --> 00:15:31.096
You punch really hard.

00:15:31.889 --> 00:15:33.265
Do we even have a boxing team?

00:15:33.349 --> 00:15:36.143
Yes! And you're the legendary member.

00:15:36.226 --> 00:15:37.436
It hurts!

00:15:38.103 --> 00:15:39.647
I'm really sorry.

00:15:39.730 --> 00:15:41.065
Wait.

00:15:42.566 --> 00:15:43.901
Something's bothering you, isn't it?

00:15:46.487 --> 00:15:47.446
Yes.

00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:51.200
I've been getting really stressed thinking about it.

00:15:51.283 --> 00:15:54.787
That's why I've become so hyper-aware of my surroundings.

00:15:58.123 --> 00:16:01.251
I knew it. The moment I saw you,

00:16:01.335 --> 00:16:03.170
Just from the way you walked, I already knew you were stressed.

00:16:04.254 --> 00:16:07.883
I was actually gonna surprise you, so your stress would wear off somehow,

00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:09.843
But I ended up getting surprised instead.

00:16:09.927 --> 00:16:12.638
I'm really sorry. Does it still hurt?

00:16:12.721 --> 00:16:14.640
Do you want me to go with you to the clinic?

00:16:16.183 --> 00:16:17.226
What?

00:16:19.269 --> 00:16:21.939
- Ouch! - Now we're even.

00:16:23.857 --> 00:16:25.609
Don't think about it anymore. It's okay.

00:16:25.693 --> 00:16:26.777
So, come on?

00:16:26.860 --> 00:16:28.028
Shall we go together?

00:16:28.112 --> 00:16:30.406
Fine, let's go then.

00:16:30.489 --> 00:16:31.365
Let's go.

00:16:32.408 --> 00:16:33.409
That really hurt.

00:18:10.923 --> 00:18:13.258
You're really amazing, sweetheart!

00:18:14.843 --> 00:18:19.389
It's okay to be sharp with knives, but be gentle with my heart.

00:18:28.941 --> 00:18:33.529
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

00:18:33.612 --> 00:18:35.864
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

00:18:50.337 --> 00:18:51.755
Son of a shark.

00:19:02.099 --> 00:19:03.350
Alexandria Cortez.

00:19:11.567 --> 00:19:12.901
Oh my God, Bok!

00:19:14.570 --> 00:19:17.739
You slept here again? You didn't go home again, Bok?

00:19:18.699 --> 00:19:19.533
My God!

00:19:19.616 --> 00:19:21.577
Bok, I didn't have a choice.

00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:24.163
I need to find out who's spying on the chief,

00:19:24.246 --> 00:19:26.373
And in order to find him or her,

00:19:26.456 --> 00:19:28.959
I need to review all the CCTV footage from that night.

00:19:29.042 --> 00:19:31.086
Find someone acting suspiciously.

00:19:31.670 --> 00:19:34.423
Bok, you do have a choice.

00:19:34.506 --> 00:19:36.508
You just don't want to choose it.

00:19:36.592 --> 00:19:39.636
You always choose the one where you have to sacrifice yourself

00:19:39.720 --> 00:19:41.180
For a greater purpose.

00:19:41.263 --> 00:19:43.098
Whatever that purpose is.

00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:45.100
Not now. I don't have time for this drama.

00:19:45.184 --> 00:19:46.226
It's not on my checklist.

00:19:46.310 --> 00:19:48.896
But this one This is what's on my checklist.

00:19:50.105 --> 00:19:54.026
I've spent hours watching the CCTV files from that night

00:19:54.109 --> 00:19:57.487
Over and over until I memorized the entire layout of the park.

00:19:59.740 --> 00:20:01.825
So, what did all that heroics get you?

00:20:07.539 --> 00:20:11.168
That person Isn't she familiar to you?

00:20:14.046 --> 00:20:15.881
How did you know that's a woman?

00:20:17.466 --> 00:20:19.301
Doesn't she look familiar to you?

00:20:23.639 --> 00:20:24.890
She does look familiar.

00:20:33.440 --> 00:20:35.108
Is there something you want to say?

00:20:36.360 --> 00:20:39.238
<i>How did she know</i> <i>that I wanted to say something?</i>

00:20:39.821 --> 00:20:41.907
<i>Can she read my mind?</i>

00:20:48.121 --> 00:20:50.165
Oh my. Really?

00:20:50.249 --> 00:20:53.168
All right, then. If you can read it, then read this.

00:20:54.962 --> 00:20:56.296
I only thought of the answer. Go!

00:20:56.380 --> 00:21:00.884
Sweetheart, even without reading what's on your mind,

00:21:00.968 --> 00:21:02.177
I already know the answer.

00:21:02.261 --> 00:21:04.304
You know it, but do I?

00:21:04.388 --> 00:21:06.014
Do I know the correct answer?

00:21:06.098 --> 00:21:07.057
That's the catch!

00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:12.854
I know I'm cute, but I'm not perfect.

00:21:13.772 --> 00:21:16.483
You're teasing me again.

00:21:17.067 --> 00:21:18.860
You're good at guessing.

00:21:18.944 --> 00:21:20.654
How did you know I wanted to tell you something?

00:21:21.321 --> 00:21:24.700
Sweetheart, I think anyone

00:21:24.783 --> 00:21:27.536
Could tell that you wanted to say something to me.

00:21:27.619 --> 00:21:30.205
You've been staring at me for a while.

00:21:30.706 --> 00:21:33.709
You don't have to use that approach on me.

00:21:41.383 --> 00:21:44.094
Nothing, I just have something on my mind.

00:21:44.177 --> 00:21:46.138
But it's nothing! Don't mind me.

00:21:47.848 --> 00:21:52.728
You know, partners should be open with each other.

00:21:53.979 --> 00:21:55.689
So, we should be open.

00:21:56.523 --> 00:21:59.609
Come on! Tell me now. What is it?

00:22:03.822 --> 00:22:06.575
Right! She does look familiar!

00:22:07.200 --> 00:22:09.536
Yes! You finally got it, right?

00:22:10.245 --> 00:22:12.247
She was also in the same area where the chief was.

00:22:12.331 --> 00:22:14.207
She never left.

00:22:14.291 --> 00:22:16.793
People already came and went around her,

00:22:16.877 --> 00:22:18.420
But she just stayed there.

00:22:20.964 --> 00:22:25.552
Watching, patiently, like a predator,

00:22:26.136 --> 00:22:28.388
Waiting for the right moment to pounce.

00:22:28.472 --> 00:22:29.765
Right.

00:22:31.683 --> 00:22:34.227
That seems familiar, Bok. There!

00:22:34.311 --> 00:22:35.854
Oh my God.

00:22:35.937 --> 00:22:38.023
She looks like Justin Bieber at Coachella,

00:22:38.106 --> 00:22:39.816
Just with a different hoodie color!

00:22:39.900 --> 00:22:41.359
Come on, Bok! What Justin Bieber?

00:22:41.443 --> 00:22:43.153
It's a woman! What's wrong with you?

00:22:43.236 --> 00:22:44.446
- A woman. - Come on!

00:22:45.072 --> 00:22:46.907
Okay. A familiar woman.

00:22:46.990 --> 00:22:49.451
There! She looks like Kendall Jenner!

00:22:49.534 --> 00:22:51.787
She just finished her nightly jog!

00:22:51.870 --> 00:22:54.456
Then she thought she'd rest for a while at the park,

00:22:54.539 --> 00:22:57.834
But because she rested at the park, she became suspicious and got judged.

00:22:59.377 --> 00:23:01.129
- Right. - Why can't you see it?

00:23:10.806 --> 00:23:12.557
I was just thinking.

00:23:13.308 --> 00:23:14.267
Don't get mad, okay?

00:23:17.354 --> 00:23:19.022
I just feel like

00:23:21.233 --> 00:23:23.026
I still don't know much about you.

00:23:23.860 --> 00:23:25.529
I still don't know much about your life.

00:23:26.863 --> 00:23:29.574
Am I making sense or not?

00:23:30.617 --> 00:23:32.536
Never mind. I knew it.

00:23:33.245 --> 00:23:34.121
No.

00:23:34.204 --> 00:23:36.873
Since our very first meeting,

00:23:36.957 --> 00:23:42.295
You already knew about me, my family, my upbringing,

00:23:42.379 --> 00:23:45.715
The family business, which you became a part of.

00:23:45.799 --> 00:23:49.219
We even had that explosive party.

00:23:51.179 --> 00:23:53.849
Just to officially introduce us

00:23:53.932 --> 00:23:57.102
As a couple to the investors and family and friends, right?

00:23:57.727 --> 00:24:00.814
I remember. It really was explosive.

00:24:02.649 --> 00:24:06.153
But what you said is true. That's all I know.

00:24:06.903 --> 00:24:07.821
You know?

00:24:07.904 --> 00:24:11.283
I still don't know Chiara outside her family.

00:24:11.366 --> 00:24:13.785
I mean, outside your business,

00:24:14.619 --> 00:24:16.204
Outside your family and friends

00:24:16.288 --> 00:24:19.207
I don't even know who Chiara is with her friends.

00:24:20.083 --> 00:24:23.712
Or just Chiara,

00:24:25.213 --> 00:24:26.673
Not Chiara Valtrovi.

00:24:28.967 --> 00:24:30.051
You know that.

00:25:12.177 --> 00:25:13.929
I'll get to know you better

00:25:14.012 --> 00:25:17.641
<i>if I spend time with the people</i> <i>you're with outside your responsibilities</i>

00:25:17.724 --> 00:25:18.892
<i>of being a Valtrovi.</i>

00:25:18.975 --> 00:25:20.852
Why don't you tell Mikoy the truth?

00:25:20.936 --> 00:25:22.896
If he truly loves you,

00:25:22.979 --> 00:25:26.191
He'll accept you wholeheartedly, with flaws and all.

00:25:29.736 --> 00:25:33.031
<i>And the person they sent</i> <i>to monitor you is him.</i>

00:25:33.114 --> 00:25:34.699
<i>Yes? Who are you?</i>

00:25:45.752 --> 00:25:47.295
<i>Mikoy, I just wanted to know.</i>

00:25:47.379 --> 00:25:48.922
How well do you know Chiara?

